10 PROPOSED COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
11 An Act relating to Alzheimer's disease and related
dementias; creating the Office of Alzheimer's Disease
12 and Related Dementia Service Coordination within the
State Department of Health; providing powers and
13 duties; establishing dementia services coordinator
position; creating the Alzheimer's Disease and
14 Related Dementia Service Coordination Revolving Fund;
specifying type of fund and source of monies; stating
15 purpose of fund; providing for expenditure of monies;
repealing 63 O.S. 2021, Sections 1-879.2 and 1-879.3,
16 which relate to Alzheimer's disease and related
dementias; providing for codification; providing an
17 effective date; and declaring an emergency.
18
19
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
21 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
22 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-879.5 of Title 63, unless
23 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
24
Req. No. 17377 Page 1

1 A. Subject to availability of funding, there is hereby created
2 within the State Department of Health the Office of Alzheimer's
3 Disease and Related Dementia Service Coordination for the purpose of
4 providing statewide coordination, service system development, and
5 information on education, support, and other available services for
6 individuals with Alzheimer's disease or related dementias and their
7 caregivers.
8 B. The Office of Alzheimer's Disease and Related Dementia
9 Service Coordination shall have the power and duty to:
10 1. Evaluate the coordination of dementia services within this
11 state and identify any duplicated services;
12 2. Coordinate informational resources affecting individuals
13 with Alzheimer's disease or related dementias and their caregivers.
14 Such coordination shall include, but not be limited to:
15 a. using dementia-related data to coordinate strategies
16 designed to improve public health outcomes and service
17 delivery for individuals with Alzheimer's disease or
18 related dementias and their caregivers,
19 b. establishing and maintaining relationships with other
20 state agencies, providers, organizations, and
21 community stakeholders to meet the needs of affected
22 populations and prevent the duplication of services,
23
24
Req. No. 17377 Page 2

1 c. supporting the provision of dementia-specific staff
2 training across all relevant state agencies and
3 organizations, and
4 d. recommending strategies to improve coordination of
5 dementia-related services and resources provided by
6 public and private entities;
7 3. Streamline all applicable state government services to
8 increase efficiency and improve the quality of dementia-related care
9 in residential, home-based, and community-based settings;
10 4. Identify grant opportunities to expand the scope of services
11 for individuals with Alzheimer's disease or related dementias and
12 their caregivers and apply for such grant opportunities;
13 5. Perform other duties relevant to supporting policy
14 development and implementation to enhance the quality of life for
15 individuals with Alzheimer's disease or related dementias and their
16 caregivers;
17 6. Promote public and professional awareness and education
18 related to Alzheimer's disease and related dementias and access to
19 needed services and programs; and
20 7. Collect and monitor data concerning the impact of
21 Alzheimer's disease and related dementias in this state.
22 C. Subject to availability of funding, the Office of
23 Alzheimer's Disease and Related Dementia Service Coordination shall
24 maintain on staff at least one dementia services coordinator. The
Req. No. 17377 Page 3

1 deme ntia services coordinator shall be a full-time, permanent
2 employee and shall be responsible for the staffing and operational
3 details of the Office.
4 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
5 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-879.6 of Title 63, unless
6 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
7 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
8 for the State Department of Health to be designated the "Alzheimer's
9 Disease and Related Dementia Service Coordination Revolving Fund".
10 The fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year
11 limitations, and shall consist of all monies received by the
12 Department from grants, gifts, and donations provided for the
13 purpose of funding the Office of Alzheimer's Disease and Related
14 Dementia Service Coordination created under Section 1 of this act.
15 All monies accruing to the credit of the fund are hereby
16 appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Department for
17 the purpose provided for in this section. Expenditures from the
18 fund shall be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer
19 against claims filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the
20 Office of Management and Enterprise Services for approval and
21 payment.
22 SECTION 3. REPEALER 63 O.S. 2021, Section 1-879.2 and 1-
23 879.3, is hereby repealed.
24 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
Req. No. 17377 Page 4

1 SECTION 5. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
2 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
3 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
4 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
